The paper deals with distributed algorithms for graph problems, specifically the maximum density subgraph problem and the lowest outdegree orientation problem. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.AL (Computational Complexity). Among these, cs.DC and cs.DS seem to be the most likely categories, as they are directly related to distributed graph algorithms. cs.NI and cs.SI are also possible categories, as the problems studied in the paper have applications in network analysis and social network analysis. Finally, cs.AL is a less likely category, as the paper does not focus on computational complexity theory, but rather on algorithm design and analysis.
